== Motivation

This documentation project is driven by both intellectual rigor and philanthropic urgency. The devastating reality of severe ME/CFS—visible through the accounts of bedbound patients who have shared their stories publicly—raises a stark question: how can biomedical research prevent deterioration into severe illness before all desire to live vanishes? Every patient has a family, children, and friends who depend on them; the stakes extend beyond individual survival to the countless lives diminished by this disease. This work aims to bridge the gap between scattered research findings and accessible, comprehensive information about ME/CFS—organizing current knowledge about symptoms, mechanisms, and treatments. By systematically analyzing what is known and identifying what must be discovered, this project seeks to serve researchers, clinicians, patients, and advocates in finding pathways out of progressive decline.

